Show HN: Two-way sync data between slack and linear
text:
Hi HN, we built a tool for teams who want a way to manage Slack conversations in Linear. Our tool will two-way sync Slack & Linear data:

1. New messages in the Slack channels you wish to sync will automatically create new issues in Linear.

2: Threaded replies in Slack reply will become a comment on the Linear ticket.

3: Adding a comment in Linear will automatically send a message to the original Slack thread.

Teams with lots of Slack messages internally and externally should find this tool useful. Eng teams can use Linear to track on-call request and manage issue status and prioritization in Linear. Product communities can use Linear as an internal ticketing platform to ensure that all customer questions receive replies.

We would love to hear any feedback or what other tools you would like to sync together. Cheers!
